<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.kevinboone.com/separation.html" class="external text" title="http://www.kevinboone.com/separation.html" rel="nofollow">"K-Zone law - Separation of Powers: the reality"</a>. Kevinboone.com<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.kevinboone.com/separation.html" class="external free" title="http://www.kevinboone.com/separation.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.kevinboone.com/separation.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-10-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=K-Zone+law+-+Separation+of+Powers%3A+the+reality&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Kevinboone.com&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kevinboone.com%2Fseparation.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Separation_of_powers"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Przeworski03importance-2">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Przeworski03importance_2-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Przeworski03importance_2-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Przeworski 2003, p.26, p.13, p.223-4</li>
<li id="cite_note-Przeworski03criminalization-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Przeworski03criminalization_3-0" title="">^</a></b> Przeworski 2003, p.14 <a href="http://assets.cambridge.org/97805218/25597/sample/9780521825597ws.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://assets.cambridge.org/97805218/25597/sample/9780521825597ws.pdf" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFCheryl_Saunders">Cheryl Saunders. <a href="http://www.adminlaw.org.uk/docs/Professor%20Cheryl%20Saunders%20-%20July%202006.doc" class="external text" title="http://www.adminlaw.org.uk/docs/Professor%20Cheryl%20Saunders%20-%20July%202006.doc" rel="nofollow">"Separation of Powers and the Judicial Branch"</a> (doc)<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.adminlaw.org.uk/docs/Professor%20Cheryl%20Saunders%20-%20July%202006.doc" class="external free" title="http://www.adminlaw.org.uk/docs/Professor%20Cheryl%20Saunders%20-%20July%202006.doc" rel="nofollow">http://www.adminlaw.org.uk/docs/Professor%20Cheryl%20Saunders%20-%20July%202006.doc</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Separation+of+Powers+and+the+Judicial+Branch&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Cheryl+Saunders&amp;rft.au=Cheryl+Saunders&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.adminlaw.org.uk%2Fdocs%2FProfessor%2520Cheryl%2520Saunders%2520-%2520July%25202006.doc&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Separation_of_powers"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> Two examples of executives of more than one person are a <a href="/wiki/Triumvirate" title="Triumvirate">triumvirate</a> (three rulers) and a <a href="/wiki/Constitutional_monarchy" title="Constitutional monarchy">constitutional monarchy</a> (two rulers).</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.fpri.org/enotes/asia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html" class="external text" title="http://www.fpri.org/enotes/asia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html" rel="nofollow">"E-Notes: Why Taiwan's Political Paralysis Persists - FPRI"</a>. Fpri.org<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.fpri.org/enotes/asia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html" class="external free" title="http://www.fpri.org/enotes/asia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.fpri.org/enotes/asia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-10-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=E-Notes%3A+Why+Taiwan%27s+Political+Paralysis+Persists+-+FPRI&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Fpri.org&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fpri.org%2Fenotes%2Fasia.20020418.rigger.taiwanpoliticalparalysis.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Separation_of_powers"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
